

	 
      How to stop erosion  Nepal is a very hilly country. More than 70% of Nepal’s land is in the Hilly region. Not long ago, Nepali people moved to the hilly region in a hope to find land which they can agriculture in. These people cut worked their blood and sweats off and they chopped the hills to make terrace. Terraces are used to protect land for erosion. When water falls in one section it then makes it’s way to another in a slow motion not causing any severe damage to the structure of land.       
    
